{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VgNWJ7gCPAvRc1xYX269ZR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ETL pipeline completed successfully. Here is the full diagnosis and resolution summary:\n\n---\n\n## Diagnosis & Fix Summary\n\n### Root Cause: Data Skew + Insufficient Executor Memory\n\n**Data skew (confirmed via `/data/skew_info.txt`):**\n- Total records: 100,000\n- `user_id 999` holds: **50,000 records (50% of all data)**\n- Skew ratio: **500x** (far beyond the 10x threshold)\n\n**Why it caused OOM:** Stage 3 does a `GROUP BY user_id`. With 50% of rows mapping to a single key, one executor receives half the dataset. At 256MB executor memory, that partition exceeds available heap and throws `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n### Fix Applied (Option C — AQE + increased executor memory)\n\nThe `etl-job.yaml` was updated with:\n```yaml\n--conf spark.executor.memory=1g                        # was 256m\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true                 # AQE on\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true        # splits hot partitions\n```\n\nAQE's skew-join handling automatically detects oversized partitions at runtime and splits them across multiple tasks, distributing `user_id=999`'s 50,000 records rather than dumping them on one executor.\n\n### Verification\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Job status | `Complete 1/1` (85s duration) |\n| All 500 tasks | Completed without OOM |\n| Final output | `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` printed |\n| Exit code | 0 (SparkContext stopped cleanly) |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1514,"cache_read_input_tokens":35724,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1514},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0d64a8aa-c3